


download latest tar and set bin to path:
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin


create a file, hello.go:
-----
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
	fmt.Printf("hello, world\n")
}
--------
Note:  hello.go need not be inside a directory named main
>go build hello.go
>./hello

=====================
struct ,array,primitives(value types)=> on assignment copy of original object returned
slice,map(pointer type)=> on assignment original object is returned(use & to point to original object)






